      "body" : "@user1382306 No it&#39;s not. That way you need to convert the whole BigDecimal into string. The BigDecimal.signum() is either using Long.signum that uses bit shifting to see if the long has a signum or BigInteger.signum() that stores the signum value in an internal int field and simply return the value of that field."
